full_text: Enough is enough. To those who are still hanging out with friends or hosting dinner parties: Do the right thing and stay home. And while you‚Äôre at home, share this video to remind others they need to stay home too. #PlankTheCurve https://t.co/b2q1fT81cO

To every university, college, polytechnic, and CEGEP in the country: We need your expertise and your resources. If you have masks and ventilators we can use, or if you think you can help with things like 3D printing of medical supplies, let us know: https://t.co/js1j1UsLlt
Now is the time to act, Canada - and we need to act together. So wash your hands. Cough into your elbow. Stay home. And listen to Dr. Tam (@CPHO_Canada). ‚§µÔ∏è https://t.co/k0FFRZCj9I

Prime Minister @AbeShinzo and I spoke yesterday about COVID-19 and the need for coordination among G7 and G20 countries. Our conversation also focused on the impacts of the virus and the work we‚Äôre doing to protect the people of Canada and Japan. More: https://t.co/9esWCHPtHN

We‚Äôre doing everything we can together to protect the health and safety of Canadians right across the country. Yesterday, @cafreeland and I spoke with premiers again about our cooperation to support everyone affected by COVID-19 and its impacts. More here: https://t.co/PqlJP2Qmq7
Let me be very clear: If you‚Äôve just returned from abroad, you must stay home and self-isolate for 14 days. This is not a suggestion. #StayAtHomeSaveLives
LIVE NOW: I‚Äôm giving an update from Rideau Cottage on the COVID-19 outbreak and what we‚Äôll be focused on when the House returns at noon. Watch here: https://t.co/Inl1HrY398
The legislation will be tabled without clause 2.

Spoke on the phone with Prime Minister @AbiyAhmedAli today. We talked about the impacts COVID-19 is having in Canada and Ethiopia, the work we‚Äôre both doing to keep people safe, and the need for international coordination. Get more details on our call: https://t.co/SRFSAhzotD

You need to stay home. And so do your friends and family members. Help spread the word with your own video - and tag your friends to remind them to stay home too. And together, we can #PlankTheCurve. @MichaelBuble and @VancityReynolds - can you help? #StayAtHomeSaveLives https://t.co/f1PQQrzMIK

To the people who seem to think they‚Äôre invincible: You‚Äôre not. So go home and stay home. You‚Äôre not just putting yourself at risk, you‚Äôre putting others at risk too - nurses and doctors, grocery store workers, your grandparents, and so many others. #StayAtHomeSaveLives

Day in and day out, farmers and food producers across the country continue to work hard so that we have good food in our stores and on our tables. So to them, we say thank you. We know you‚Äôre dealing with the impacts of COVID-19 just like the rest of us, and we‚Äôve got your back.

We have some of the world‚Äôs brightest researchers right here at home, and many of them are stepping up to join the fight against COVID-19. To help them take on this challenge, we‚Äôre announcing direct financial support for vaccine development and production in Canada.

WATCH LIVE: I‚Äôm speaking from Rideau Cottage about the evolving COVID-19 situation and the work we‚Äôre doing to help everyone - from researchers and scientists to farmers and food producers. Tune in here: https://t.co/CjCethMq3r

From my family to yours, and to all the kids who‚Äôve had to sacrifice their play dates with friends and didn‚Äôt get the March Break they‚Äôd hoped for, thank you for doing your part. We‚Äôre going to get through this together. https://t.co/u5Trx1rRXq

If you think you might have COVID-19 but aren‚Äôt sure what to do, use @GovCanHealth‚Äôs self-assessment tool. It‚Äôll help determine if you should be tested for the virus and give you the contact information you may need. It‚Äôs available online here: https://t.co/Vj3ZpmwSLV https://t.co/LrwQBnGrB6

Whether you‚Äôre a parent worried about paying for rent and groceries, or you‚Äôre a small business owner worried about paying your bills and your staff, know that we‚Äôll do whatever it takes to get you the help you need. That‚Äôs why we‚Äôve asked that the House of Commons be recalled.

HAPPENING NOW: I‚Äôm giving an update from Rideau Cottage on the COVID-19 outbreak and what we‚Äôll be focused on in the coming days and weeks to support you and keep you safe. Watch live for more info: https://t.co/EE00rplDEL

Are you a Canadian who‚Äôs abroad right now? If you‚Äôre looking to come home, please register with @TravelGoC so we can get you important information as quickly as possible. You can do this online at: https://t.co/VVNyhIcCKu

As we work to bring home Canadians stranded abroad, I want say thanks to the airport staff and @CanBorder personnel who will be greeting them when they land. Thank you for your professionalism, your dedication, and for always rising to the challenge.

#SaturdayThoughts: 

Do your part to help slow the spread of #COVID19 and #PlankTheCurve:

Wash your hands üßºüëè

Whether you‚Äôre here at home or currently abroad, we‚Äôre doing everything we can to support you and keep you safe. To those who are stranded abroad, we‚Äôre working with Canadian airlines to bring you home. And we‚Äôre doing our best to reach as many of you as we can.
